Interface ITransientCollection<K>

  • Type Parameters:
    K -
    All Superinterfaces:

    All Known Subinterfaces:

    All Known Implementing Classes:
    TransientHashSet, TransientList, TransientQueue, TransientTreeSet, TransientVector

    public interface ITransientCollection<K>
extends Collection<K>
    ITransientCollection hierarchy defines classes which, in general are extensions of regular Java collections classes but have a pure constructor (taking a Seq or an IPersistent something), and have the persistent() method below. This means that you can use the existing Java collections classes as @MutableUnshareds.
    Author:
    robmoffat
